  <prompt>Mandatory wrap-up (per task-create Step 3.7): (1) Run `/code-review` on the full PR diff vs master. (2) Run `/adr-check` on the full PR diff vs master. (3) Update `README.md` status → "Complete". (4) Create `projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r2/notes/lessons-learned.md` capturing what worked (Theme A.2 Meter consolidation impact, etc.), what surprised us, and recommendations for future Redis/observability work. (5) Update `projects/INDEX.md` registry — remove R2 from Active table (per maintenance contract) OR move to Archived section (per `devops-project-archive` convention, if registry has one). (6) Run `/repo-cleanup` to remove ephemeral files. (7) Verify PR is mergeable + all checks pass.</prompt>
  <role>Project close-out operator. Apply `task-execute` skill at FULL rigor + invoke `code-review`, `adr-check`, `repo-cleanup` skills.</role>
  <goal>R2 PR merged + project marked Complete. lessons-learned.md committed. INDEX.md cleaned. Repo state clean. R8 (or whatever R3 is) can pick up cleanly.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Last task of the project. After this, sister projects can rely on R2 being closed and shipped.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r2/README.md (UPDATE status to Complete)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r2/notes/lessons-learned.md (NEW)</file>
      <file>projects/INDEX.md (REMOVE R2 row OR move to Archived section)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="task-create">Step 3.7 mandatory wrap-up.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">G-15 — build clean + tests at baseline maintained.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r2/spec.md</file>
