  <steps>
    <step order="1">Run `/code-review` on the R2 PR diff vs master.</step>
    <step order="2">Run `/adr-check` on the R2 PR diff vs master (focus on ADR-009 untouched + ADR-010 alignment + ADR-029 publish-size).</step>
    <step order="3">Address any review findings (loop back to relevant tasks if needed).</step>
    <step order="4">Update README.md Status → Complete.</step>
    <step order="5">Author `notes/lessons-learned.md` with: (a) what worked (e.g., Meter consolidation cleaned up DI surface; static class outcome matched ADR-010); (b) what surprised us (e.g., consumer count for CacheMetrics; live-customer audit for customer.bicep); (c) recommendations (e.g., for R3 / future Redis observability work).</step>
    <step order="6">Update `projects/INDEX.md` — remove R2 row from Active table (R1 was kept in Active even when complete; follow same convention OR move to Archived if convention exists at time).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `/repo-cleanup`.</step>
    <step order="8">Final `dotnet build` + `dotnet test` + `Deploy-BffApi.ps1` smoke if dev still available — confirm baseline maintained.</step>
    <step order="9">Update current-task.md status to "PROJECT COMPLETE" + reset.</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX 🔲 → ✅ for task 032.</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
